reviews.text: I love the scallop and mushroom spaghetti. Surprisingly high quality dish. The source is so tasteful that we have to order more bread so I can finish up the source.

This chain of cafe serves European (not sure if it's French?) style coffe, drinks, sandwiches, pasta, and sometimes risotto. Dishes are a bit adapted for local people. Quality is generally fine or better. Portion is average to small. This shop is relatively large in this chain. Seats are generally comfortable and available. Can sit leisurely for a tea break or chat. May cost like HKD60-100 for lunch.
Very French. Disinterested service, overpriced and bad coffee. Nice place to sit and relax.
Decent food, they under charge me for some reason, and the coffee and croissants are really quite good.  Nobody is shooing you out of your perch either.

14 Feb 19: lunch with teammates today, today is Valentines’s Day, so we cannot use the $50 coupon from buying the set lunch. We love to lunch here, it was because no many people, no need to queue and a quick bite is allow. 

The foods come to us within 15 mins, sandwiches are always delicious, we love to order. Cream macaroni always better than tomato sauce one. We ordered 2 2-people sets, it is too full for 4 people (3 ladies + 1 gentlemen), maybe we ordered too many breads, the soup also come with a breadstick and no ice cream for today, therefore they gave a blueberries cakes for us. Except too many breads, overall is good, will come again.

reviews.text: 價錢較高，而且食品也不值這水平，如早餐的珍寶腸，感覺如超市的平宜貨，火雞片也只是薄薄一片，有會員優惠，但有點複雜，而且只開了一個收銀機，大大增加客人排隊的時間，是地方比較舒適和比較易找到位子才來
牛角酥的質素冇之前咁好，雞扒又細佐，如果冇優惠券，早餐價錢係尖東最貴！
I love the scallop and mushroom spaghetti. Surprisingly high quality dish. The source is so tasteful that we have to order more bread so I can finish up the source.
食物分量好少兼價錢頗貴，湯是凍的
今早的早餐做得很差。牛角包。煙肉焗到黑色。
